column2: This report of Vital Statistics death data is a point-in-time snapshot of the total number of deaths attributed to the 30 most common causes of death in 2022 according to Statistics Canada as of September 18th, 2023. These totals and the ranking of the most common causes of death will change over time as investigations into deaths are concluded, final causes of death are determined, and Statistics Canada completes its coding of deaths based on information received by the province. Information in this report is not updated throughout the year.

This report of Vital Statistics death data is a point-in-time snapshot of the total number of deaths attributed to the 30 most common causes of death in 2022 according to Statistics Canada as of September 18th, 2023. These totals and the ranking of the most common causes of death will change over time as investigations into deaths are concluded, final causes of death are determined, and Statistics Canada completes its coding of deaths based on information received by the province. Information in this report is not updated throughout the year.
